SKILL|heartmula|"HeartMuLa: Suno-like song generation from lyrics + tags."
STEP|1|**HeartMuLa** - Music language model (3B/7B) for generation from lyrics + tags
STEP|2|**HeartCodec** - 12.5Hz music codec for high-fidelity audio reconstruction
STEP|3|**HeartTranscriptor** - Whisper-based lyrics transcription
STEP|4|**HeartCLAP** - Audio-text alignment model
STEP|5|User wants to generate music/songs from text descriptions
STEP|6|User wants an open-source Suno alternative
STEP|7|User wants local/offline music generation
STEP|8|User asks about HeartMuLa, heartlib, or AI music generation
STEP|9|**Minimum**: 8GB VRAM with `--lazy_load true` (loads/unloads models sequentially)
STEP|10|**Recommended**: 16GB+ VRAM for comfortable single-GPU usage
STEP|11|**Multi-GPU**: Use `--mula_device cuda:0 --codec_device cuda:1` to split across GPUs
STEP|12|3B model with lazy_load peaks at ~6.2GB VRAM
STEP|13|.venv/bin/activate
STEP|14|IMPORTANT**: As of Feb 2026, the pinned dependencies have conflicts with newer packages. Apply these fixes:
STEP|15|Patch 1 - RoPE cache fix** in `src/heartlib/heartmula/modeling_heartmula.py`:
STEP|16|Why**: `from_pretrained` creates model on meta device first; `Llama3ScaledRoPE.rope_init()` skips cache building on meta tensors, then never rebuilds after weights are loaded to real device.
STEP|17|Patch 2 - HeartCodec loading fix** in `src/heartlib/pipelines/music_generation.py`:
STEP|18|Why**: VQ codebook `initted` buffers have shape `[1]` in checkpoint vs `[]` in model. Same data, just scalar vs 0-d tensor. Safe to ignore.
STEP|19|The installed `torch==2.4.1` includes CUDA 12.1 support out of the box
STEP|20|`torchtune` may report version `0.4.0+cpu` — this is just package metadata, it still uses CUDA via PyTorch
STEP|21|To verify GPU is being used, look for "CUDA memory" lines in the output (e.g. "CUDA memory before unloading: 6.20 GB")
STEP|22|**No GPU?** You can run on CPU with `--mula_device cpu --codec_device cpu`, but expect generation to be **extremely slow** (potentially 30-60+ minutes for a single song vs ~4 minutes on GPU). CPU mode
STEP|23|.venv/bin/activate
STEP|24|Tags** (comma-separated, no spaces):
STEP|25|Lyrics** (use bracketed structural tags):
STEP|26|RTF (Real-Time Factor) ≈ 1.0 — a 4-minute song takes ~4 minutes to generate
STEP|27|Output: MP3, 48kHz stereo, 128kbps
STEP|28|**Do NOT use bf16 for HeartCodec** — degrades audio quality. Use fp32 (default).
STEP|29|**Tags may be ignored** — known issue (#90). Lyrics tend to dominate; experiment with tag ordering.
STEP|30|**Triton not available on macOS** — Linux/CUDA only for GPU acceleration.
STEP|31|**RTX 5080 incompatibility** reported in upstream issues.
STEP|32|The dependency pin conflicts require the manual upgrades and patches described above.
STEP|33|Repo: https://github.com/HeartMuLa/heartlib
STEP|34|Models: https://huggingface.co/HeartMuLa
STEP|35|Paper: https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.10547
STEP|36|License: Apache-2.0
